The paper is about the theoretical analysis of the restricted Boltzmann machine, which is a fundamental building block of deep learning models. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of the machine using the CD-1 procedure, which involves optimization and information theory. Hence, it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.IT (Information Theory), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
